label.value: microtiter plate biofilm assay evidence used in manual assertion

value.value: A type of microtiter plate biofilm assay evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

label.value: air-liquid interface assay evidence

value.value: A type of biofilm formation assay evidence in which biofilm formation is analyzed, without staining, over 4 to 48 hours by growth on a tilted multiwell plate.

definition.value: Tilting of the plate positions the air-liquid interface on a clear portion to improve visability.

label.value: air-liquid interface assay evidence used in manual assertion

value.value: A type of air-liquid interface assay evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

label.value: colony biofilm assay evidence

value.value: A type of biofilm formation assay evidence in which a colony is grown on a semipermeable membrane on an agar plate. The plate serves to supply nutrients and the semipermeable membrane can be relocated to fresh plates.

definition.value: The plates commonly contain different carbon sources or antibiotic treatments to observe properties of the cells.

label.value: colony biofilm assay evidence used in manual assertion

value.value: A type of colony biofilm assay evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

label.value: Kadouri drip-fed biofilm assay evidence

value.value: A type of biofilm formation assay evidence in which mature bacterial biofilms are grown in a multiwell plate that has a growth medium continually pumped through the wells while waste is continually pumped out.

label.value: Kadouri drip-fed biofilm assay evidence used in manual assertion

label.value: optogenetic evidence

value.value: A type of experimental phenotypic evidence arising from experiment in which neuronal activity is manipulated using genetically encoded, optically activated neuronal actuators.

label.value: optogenetic evidence used in manual assertion

value.value: A type of optogenetic evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

label.value: fluorescent sensor evidence

value.value: A type of fluorescence evidence that is based on direct, quantitative measurement of some cellular property using a fluorescent sensor.

definition.value: Examples include sensors for ion concentration and potential difference across a membrane.

label.value: fluorescent sensor evidence used in manual assertion

value.value: A type of fluorescent sensor evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

label.value: genetically encoded fluorescent sensor evidence

value.value: A type of fluorescent sensor evidence that is based on direct, quantitative measurement of some cellular property using a genetically encoded fluorescent sensor.

label.value: genetically encoded fluorescent electrophysiology assay evidence

value.value: A type of fluorescent sensor evidence and electrophysiology assay evidence where the electrical properties of cells or tissues are studied using fluorescent sensors.

definition.value: Examples include genetically encoded sensors that detect potential difference across plasma membrane.

label.value: genetically encoded fluorescent electrophysiology assay evidence used in manual assertion

value.value: A type of genetically encoded fluorescent electrophysiology assay evidence that is used in a manual assertion.

label.value: genetically encoded fluorescent ion concentration sensor assay evidence

value.value: A type of genetically encoded fluorescent electrophysiology assay evidence that is based on direct, quantitative measurement of ion concentration using a genetically encoded fluorescent sensor.

definition.value: Examples include the genetically encoded calcium indicator GCaMP.

label.value: extracellular recording evidence

label.value: high throughput evidence

value.value: A type of evidence where data generation is automated with equipment to allow for assaying samples or molecules in parallel.

definition.value: Some relevant articles include: PMID:23340846, doi:10.1038/nmeth0607-523

label.value: high throughput evidence used in manual assertion

label.value: high throughput cell biology evidence

value.value: A type of high throughput evidence where a classical cell biology technique is automated with equipment to allow for assaying biomolecules in parallel.

definition.value: HT methodologies may incorporate techniques from optics, chemistry, biology or image analysis (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/High_throughput_biology)

label.value: high throughput cell biology evidence used in manual assertion

label.value: immunofluorescence wide-field microscopy evidence used in manual assertion

label.value: wide-field fluorescence microscopy evidence used in manual assertion

value.value: A type of wide-field microscopy evidence that is used in a manual assertion where pure white and ultraviolet light are produced by a mercury lamp, passed through an optical filter (excitation filter), and directed to a sample via a dichroic mirror, followed by detection of the fluorescent light by a camera after it passes through an emission filter.

label.value: over expression analysis evidence used in manual assertion

value.value: A type of experimental phenotypic evidence that is used in a manual assertion where a gene and/or gene product is investigated in a transgenic organism that has been engineered to overexpress that gene product.

label.value: fluorescence recovery after photobleaching evidence

value.value: A type of fluorescence evidence where quantitative information on the diffusion properties of a sample is produced from the measurement of diffusion of fluorescent probes over time into an area that has been photobleached by a high-intensity laser pulse.
FRAP is a fluorescence microscopy-based technique.
